An example of provisioning EC2 instances with user data scripts to initializing,
this example assumes that there is an existing s3 bucket containing an
application binary.

The s3 bucket must have account regional namespace, with the bucket name prefix
being `application-bin`, and the application binary file in that bucket must
have the name `app`. So the full s3 bucket object path would look something
like: `s3://application-bin-000000000000-us-east-1-an/app`

A VPC endpoint was provisioned because the instance on which the application
will be run is deployed on a private subnet (intra subnet) without a NAT gateway
to outside internet, a VPC endpoint allows such an instance to connect to s3
bucket, the instance in the private subnet can be completely isolated from the
outside world while still being able to fetch from an s3 bucket.

This could be improved by having a `variables.tf` and allow a user to provide
the s3 bucket object as an argument.
